@piquark6046 Don't you too often ignore comments which sometimes are important? Plus, regarding `##button.MuiButtonBase-root.MuiIconButton-root:has(> svg[data-testid="ShareRoundedIcon"])` where's the need for `:has()`? Do not use `:has()` if the end result is the same without it.

@Alex-302 I wonder about our policy for URL-copy buttons. I haven't regarded them as share-buttons, in fact, here the rest of buttons are hidden by `##.react-share__ShareButton`. I'm unsure if these are what all the user expect Social lists to block. Though user can copy the url from the address bar, they are utility similar to go-to-top buttons. Addressing 
copy buttons requires many more additional rules which bloats our list.

@AdamWr IIRC, several years ago you didn't actively hide copy buttons and sometimes even exempted, but nowadays tend to hide? Was there a change in your mind or in our policy?

Personally, I think we don't have to actively block them, unless, rule-wise, it's much easier to hide together when we target SNS buttons.

